# Keep the Docker build context small and deterministic.
# The build copies project files explicitly and restores inside the image, so
# nothing local from bin/obj or tooling caches should ever be sent to the daemon.

## .NET build output
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/publish/
artifacts/

## Distribution / release artifacts
releases/
Releases/
*.nupkg
*.snupkg

## Git & CI metadata (not needed inside the image)
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github/

## IDE / editor
.vs/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.user
*.suo
*.userosscache
*.userprefs

## Docker / compose (don't recurse the build into itself)
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose.yml
.env
.env.example

## Helm chart (not part of the image build context)
helm/

## OS noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

## Logs
*.log
logs/

## Docs & images (not needed to build the bot)
docs/
*.md
